measure.name: df_lighting_control
measure.description: This measure implements demand flexibility measure on daily lighting control with load shed strategy, by adjusting Lighting Power Density (reflecting lighting dimming) corresponding to the peak schedule based on daily peak load prediction.

argument.name: demand_flexibility_objective
argument.display_name: Objective of demand flexibility control (peak load reduction, peak emission reduction, utility bill cost saving, operational cost saving)

argument.name: light_adjustment_method
argument.display_name: Method of lighting dimming (absolute change, relative change)

argument.name: light_adjustment
argument.display_name: Percentage to decrease light dimming/LPD by (0-100)

argument.name: num_timesteps_in_hr
argument.display_name: Number/Count of timesteps in an hour for sample simulations

argument.name: load_prediction_method
argument.display_name: Method of load prediction (full baseline run, bin sample, part year bin sample, fixed schedule, outdoor air temperature-based)

argument.name: peak_lag
argument.display_name: Time lag of peak responding to temperature peak (hour), for oat prediction method only

argument.name: peak_window_strategy
argument.display_name: Method of determining peak windows (max savings, start with peak, end with peak, center with peak)
